data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync Cosmos DB calls will throw at runtime — with no opt-in to restore them.**

In EF Core 10, sync I/O on the Cosmos provider was unsupported by default but you could re-enable it. **EF Core 11 removes that opt-in entirely.** `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` against Cosmos now always throw.

**Fix — convert to async:**

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This is a **medium-impact** change. You'll also need to update all callers to `await` these methods and propagate `async`/`Task` up the call chain. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
